  "metadata": {
    "copy": {
      "alternate_titles": [
        "The Therac-25 Failure Was a Trust Failure",
        "When Software Graded Its Own Safety",
        "Therac-25 and the Warning No One Could Prove",
        "The Radiation Machine That Said Nothing Was Wrong"
      ],
      "chapters": [
        {
          "summary": "A treatment room contradiction opens the case.",
          "time": "00:00",
          "title": "Patient or Machine"
        },
        {
          "summary": "Radiation therapy depends on mode and hardware matching.",
          "time": "01:15",
          "title": "The Narrow Margin"
        },
        {
          "summary": "Proven code inherits trust from hardware that no longer exists.",
          "time": "02:47",
          "title": "The Safety Net Removed"
        },
        {
          "summary": "Fast edits expose a software state the console cannot admit.",
          "time": "04:29",
          "title": "The Hidden State"
        },
        {
          "summary": "Routine sessions train the system to believe the machine.",
          "time": "06:24",
          "title": "How Trust Repeats"
        },
        {
          "summary": "Separate hospitals see the same impossible injury.",
          "time": "09:14",
          "title": "The Pattern Repeats"
        },
        {
          "summary": "The case breaks open when testing asks how the machine can fail.",
          "time": "12:00",
          "title": "The Burden of Proof"
        },
        {
          "summary": "The lesson moves from one machine to any system that grades itself.",
          "time": "15:04",
          "title": "Trust Is Not Safety"
        }
      ],
      "description": "A patient is injured by a radiation therapy machine, but the machine reports that nothing happened.\nThis Cascade Effects video follows the Therac-25 accidents through the software race condition, missing hardware interlocks, operator warnings, and institutional trust that let the same failure repeat.\n\nChapters:\n00:00 Patient or Machine\n01:15 The Narrow Margin\n02:47 The Safety Net Removed\n04:29 The Hidden State\n06:24 How Trust Repeats\n09:14 The Pattern Repeats\n12:00 The Burden of Proof\n15:04 Trust Is Not Safety\n\nReferences:\nNancy Leveson and Clark Turner, An Investigation of the Therac-25 Accidents\nComputing Cases, Therac-25 case materials and operator-interface notes\n\n#Therac25 #SoftwareSafety #MedicalDevices",
